                                      ModifiesViewForAllExporters Property

  ----------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Controls when [ModifyViewBeforeGeneration(Document, View,
Nullable[]{#LST49F7B4C5_1}](3c32f9fb-1932-8256-6efb-d7c3cc1cb070.htm)

ModelDataExportFormat[]{#LST49F7B4C5_2}

, String[]{#LST49F7B4C5_3}

) and [ModifyViewAfterPublish(Document, View,
Nullable[]{#LST49F7B4C5_4}](c56e5879-029d-be92-2a9c-02be281a7e96.htm)

ModelDataExportFormat[]{#LST49F7B4C5_5}

, String[]{#LST49F7B4C5_6}

) should be called when processing [View]{.nolink}s.

- [[]{#LST49F7B4C5_7}]{.keyword}
  = Methods are called before and after (respectively) exporters are
  processed such that any modifications made by this object are picked
  up by all.
- [[]{#LST49F7B4C5_8}]{.keyword}
  = Methods are called immediately before and after (respectively) this
  exporter so that any modifications are only applicable to this object.

If this object never modifies [View]{.nolink}s before they are exported,
this should return [[]{#LST49F7B4C5_9}]{.keyword}

.
:::

  ----------------------------------- --------------------------------------
  ![](../icons/Help.png)              PointExportMethods[]{#LST4261CF9A_0}
                                      
                                      ExportToFile Method

  ----------------------------------- --------------------------------------

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Writes the provided [points]{.parameter} to a file and returns the full
name of resulting file name if the process completed successfully,
otherwise [null]{.code}. Any I/O errors are thrown in a failure to write
the file.

In the event (via values provided by [includeExtensions]{.parameter}
and/or [disableExtensions]{.parameter}) no exporters are available - the
user is presented a dialog which doesn\'t allow a file extension and
will fail if they try to continue.
:::

    String\
    (Optional) Filename of target to write to. If left out, the user
    will be prompted for one with a save dialog form and (if successful)
    this value will be returned. Any unsupported file extensions will
    throw a [FormatException]{.nolink}

[includeExtensions]{.parameter} (Optional)
:   Type:Â [System.Collections.Generic[]{#LST4261CF9A_8}]{.nolink}
    IEnumerable[]{#LST4261CF9A_9}
    [String]{.nolink}[]{#LST4261CF9A_10}
    \
    (Optional) If provided, includes only the exporters matching the
    provided file extensions. If not provided, all exporters are
    enabled. For example, providing \".csv\" as the only value would
    make it the only option presented to the user.

[disableExtensions]{.parameter} (Optional)

    \
    (Optional) If provided, disables exporters matching the provided
    file extensions. For example, providing an entry for \".csv\" would
    prevent the CSV exporter from being available.

    This takes priority over [includeExtensions]{.parameter} if the same
    value is provided in both.

#### Parameters {#parameters .subHeading}

[document]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [Document]{.nolink}\
    Revit document to query.

[direction]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [eVolve.Core.Revit.Integration[]{#LSTA6B1D8B3_3}](0f330211-d3fb-3b01-532a-4edc4f684db6.htm)
    API[]{#LSTA6B1D8B3_4}
    ProfileDirection\
    The direction which [DataProfileDefinition]{.nolink} must be
    configured for.

[featureId]{.parameter}

:   Type:Â [System[]{#LSTA6B1D8B3_5}](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.string){target="_blank"
    rel="noopener noreferrer"}

    String\
    Identifier of a feature provided to
    [RegisterImplementingFeature(String,
    String)](9c6cb567-5f7f-d911-33e1-408fb2c0830d.htm) or
    [[]{#LSTA6B1D8B3_6}]{.keyword}

    if not registered.

    The return will be limited to [DataProfileDefinition]{.nolink}s
    containing the provided value in its [FeatureIds]{.nolink} or
    containing no entries in [FeatureIds]{.nolink} at all.

    To ignore this filter entirely, provide
    [IgnoreProfileNamesFeatureIdFilter](25eba657-b745-e883-fc7f-a32054950d89.htm).

[selectionListId]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [System[]{#LSTA6B1D8B3_7}](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.string){target="_blank"
    rel="noopener noreferrer"}
    String\
    Identifier of a selection list provided to
    [RegisterFieldColumnNamesSelectionList(String, String,
    IEnumerable[]{#LSTA6B1D8B3_8}](c90f93ac-8fb5-6e8e-1fea-f2fe08ae76e7.htm)
    String[]{#LSTA6B1D8B3_9}
    ).
    If specified the return will be limited to only
    [DataProfileDefinition]{.nolink}s which have this exact match
    configured as its [ColumnNameSelectionList]{.nolink}. Provide
    [[]{#LSTA6B1D8B3_10}]{.keyword}
    to ignore.

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary

An implementation must define how a user configures an individual entry
as well as how that entry processes files.

To make available for consumption, implementers should call
[RegisterModelDataExportDestination[]{#LST9C059444_0}](b482a54b-3487-cc6e-4bde-1f6ea3ca652a.htm)

T[]{#LST9C059444_1}

  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Publishes the specified [view]{.parameter} to the provided
[exportDestination]{.parameter} using the options provided. Returns if
the operation succeeded with any unexpected errors being thrown.

This operation is self-contained in that it will perform the full
publish process (initialization and finalization included) defined by
[exportDestination]{.parameter} during publish.

::: {#ID3RBSection .collapsibleSection}
The return is the same structure used by [WriteData(Document, String,
Dictionary[]{#LST323AA73E_26}](b6176786-e28e-6c39-c37a-42cce47f1470.htm)

String, Dictionary[]{#LST323AA73E_27}

String, String[]{#LST323AA73E_28}

[]{#LST323AA73E_29}

, Boolean, API[]{#LST323AA73E_30}

UnmappedFieldAction, []{#LST323AA73E_31}

String[]{#LST323AA73E_32}

[]{#LST323AA73E_33}

, API[]{#LST323AA73E_34}

OnElementProcessed).

It contains a lookup with each matching item\'s [UniqueId]{.nolink} as
the outer key with the inner data being a lookup of each fully resolved
[DataProfileFieldDefinition]{.nolink}. The key for the inner lookup is
the [ColumnName]{.nolink} and the value is the fully resolved/expanded
[ParameterName]{.nolink} value.

When [SpecialParameterName]{.nolink} values are used, it is possible
that a single [Element]{.nolink} could produce multiple rows. When this
occurs the respective key of the return modifies the [UniqueId]{.nolink}
value of the \"extra\" rows to include a suffix. Use the
[GetUniqueId(String)](9303b41f-11e9-0689-b3f4-134757b71ee8.htm) method
to guarantee the appropriate [UniqueId]{.nolink} is pulled for each
respective entry.
:::

                                      ModifyViewAfterPublish Method

  ----------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Called after the output of the [view]{.parameter} has been published by
this module and returns if [view]{.parameter} was modified by this
method.

This method\'s actions should be in consideration of the
implementation\'s
[ModifiesViewForAllExporters](a894278c-6ea6-8c11-a189-efa99f2ddf0f.htm).

If this implementation does not modify the sheet, it should return
[[]{#LST456290D1_1}]{.keyword}

.

This method should handle its own exceptions and prevent them from
bubbling up.
:::

                                      GetLocation Method

  ----------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Prompts the user to pick a destination location and returns the
selection. If no selection is made, [[]{#LST566919CD_1}]{.keyword}

should be returned.

The return value does not need to be human readable (this will be
handled by [GetLocationDisplay(Document, String,
String[]{#LST566919CD_2}](909b6e13-a82c-a2d0-661c-95d794e15127.htm)

)). It should be in a format that can be provided later for consumption.
:::

#### Parameters {#parameters .subHeading}

:   Type:Â [Document]{.nolink}\
    The current Revit document.

[uniqueId]{.parameter}

:   Type:Â [System[]{#LST10C738B4_1}]{.nolink}

    String\
    The Revit [UniqueId]{.nolink} which sourced the [file]{.parameter}
    being processed.

    This can be used to retrieve additional details about the record
    from Revit if it is needed for processing.

[location]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [System[]{#LST10C738B4_2}]{.nolink}
    String\
    The non-[[]{#LST10C738B4_3}]{.keyword}
    location value previously selected by [GetLocation(IWin32Window,
    Document, String)](f45e491f-1810-bb55-0c23-3607b791965a.htm) which
    defines the destination.

[file]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [System[]{#LST10C738B4_4}]{.nolink}
    String\

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Converts the results of a call to [GetData(Document, String,
API[]{#LST68560586_1}](f86bc016-0809-33e6-d510-830cd878ea77.htm)

OnElementProcessed) to a
[DataTable](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.data.datatable){target="_blank"
rel="noopener noreferrer"}.

- Each key of the inner lookup is used as the respective
  [DataColumn](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.data.datacolumn){target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"} name with the type being
  [string]{.keyword}.
- The outer lookup key is stored in a
  [string]{.keyword}[DataColumn](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.data.datacolumn){target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"} named
  [IdColumnName](feaaafa7-1248-d5d8-f0e8-aea7c3d907ee.htm).

If [data]{.parameter} does not contain any entries then an empty table
is returned.

count of the number of records processed.

Only [Element]{.nolink}s which match the source
[SelectionFilter]{.nolink} are processed.

                                      ModifyViewAfterPublish Method

  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Called after the output of the [view]{.parameter} has been published by
this module and returns if [view]{.parameter} was modified by this
method.

This method\'s actions should be in consideration of the
implementation\'s
[ModifiesViewForAllExporters](a894278c-6ea6-8c11-a189-efa99f2ddf0f.htm).

If this implementation does not modify the sheet, it should return
[[]{#LSTE471BDF9_1}]{.keyword}

.

This method should handle its own exceptions and prevent them from
bubbling up.
:::

                                      Method

  ----------------------------------- ---------------------------------------

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Registers an entry which will be available for users to select when
defining an [DataProfileDefinition]{.nolink}. When the provided
[displayName]{.parameter} entry is selected, the respective
[fieldColumnNames]{.parameter} sources a list of predefined
[ColumnName]{.nolink} values a user can pick when defining mappings
which have the [ColumnNameSelectionList]{.nolink} set to
[id]{.parameter}.
:::

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Sets the [StatusParameterName]{.nolink} to [status]{.parameter} for the
provided [spool]{.parameter} and returns if it was assigned without
error.

The return value is only with respect to assignment to
[spool]{.parameter} itself. If [pushToParts]{.parameter} is
[[]{#LST741F3723_1}]{.keyword}

and assignment fails on any members, this will not impact the return
value.


:::::::
:::::::::::

#### Parameters {#parameters .subHeading}

[spool]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [AssemblyInstance]{.nolink}\
    The spool to set the status of.

[status]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [System[]{#LST741F3723_2}]{.nolink}
    String\
    Value to set to [StatusParameterName]{.nolink}.

[pushToParts]{.parameter} (Optional)

:   Type:Â [System[]{#LST741F3723_3}]{.nolink}

    Nullable[]{#LST741F3723_4}

    [Boolean]{.nolink}[]{#LST741F3723_5}

    \
    (Optional)

    ::: summary
    Indicates whether parameter value updates should be applied to spool
    and parts ([[]{#LST741F3723_6}]{.keyword}
    ) or to the spool only ([[]{#LST741F3723_7}]{.keyword}
    ).
    :::

    .

    If this is not provided, the current
    [SpoolingConfigurationDataBase]{.nolink} is loaded and the value is
    read from it.

[elements]{.parameter} (Optional)

:   Type:Â [System.Collections.Generic[]{#LST741F3723_8}]{.nolink}

    IEnumerable[]{#LST741F3723_9}

    [Element]{.nolink}[]{#LST741F3723_10}

    \
    (Optional) Only used when [pushToParts]{.parameter} is
    [[]{#LST741F3723_11}]{.keyword}

    .

Dictionary[]{#LST157B7874_26}](b6176786-e28e-6c39-c37a-42cce47f1470.htm)

[]{#LST157B7874_33}

, API[]{#LST157B7874_34}

OnElementProcessed).

It contains a lookup with each matching item\'s [UniqueId]{.nolink} as
the outer key with the inner data being a lookup of each fully resolved
[DataProfileFieldDefinition]{.nolink}. The key for the inner lookup is
the [ColumnName]{.nolink} and the value is the fully resolved/expanded
[ParameterName]{.nolink} value.

When [SpecialParameterName]{.nolink} values are used, it is possible
that a single [Element]{.nolink} could produce multiple rows. When this
occurs the respective key of the return modifies the [UniqueId]{.nolink}
value of the \"extra\" rows to include a suffix. Use the
[GetUniqueId(String)](9303b41f-11e9-0689-b3f4-134757b71ee8.htm) method
to guarantee the appropriate [UniqueId]{.nolink} is pulled for each
respective entry.

``` {xml:space="preserve"}
Public Delegate Function OnElementProcessed ( 
    totalElements As Integer,
    recordNumber As Integer,
    element As Element,
    fieldData As Dictionary(Of String, String),
    stopProcessingFields As HashSet(Of String)
) As Boolean
```
:::
:::::::
:::::::::::

#### Parameters {#parameters .subHeading}

[totalElements]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [System[]{#LST7553ACFD_2}](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.int32){target="_blank"
    rel="noopener noreferrer"}
    Int32\
    The total elements being processed.

[recordNumber]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [System[]{#LST7553ACFD_3}](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.int32){target="_blank"
    rel="noopener noreferrer"}
    Int32\
    The current record number being processed. This will be between 1
    and [totalElements]{.parameter}.

[element]{.parameter}

:   Type:Â [Element]{.nolink}\
    The just finished processing element. It is possible this could be
    [[]{#LST7553ACFD_4}]{.keyword}

    if a record sent for processing no longer exists or is not
    applicable to the processing criteria.

    It is also possible this could be provided more than once if the
    respective element generated multiple rows.

[fieldData]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [System.Collections.Generic[]{#LST7553ACFD_5}](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.collections.generic.dictionary-2){target="_blank"
    rel="noopener noreferrer"}
    Dictionary[]{#LST7553ACFD_6}
    [String](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.string){target="_blank"
    rel="noopener noreferrer"},
    [String](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.string){target="_blank"
    rel="noopener noreferrer"}[]{#LST7553ACFD_7}
    \
    The resulting/source inner data entry (depending on the context
    direction) from the processing of [element]{.parameter}.

[stopProcessingFields]{.parameter}
:   Type:Â [System.Collections.Generic[]{#LST7553ACFD_8}](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.collections.generic.hashset-1){target="_blank"
    rel="noopener noreferrer"}
    HashSet[]{#LST7553ACFD_9}
    [String](https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/api/system.string){target="_blank"
    rel="noopener noreferrer"}[]{#LST7553ACFD_10}
    \
    Contains a list of key values from [fieldData]{.parameter} which are
    no longer being processed. Adding or removing entries to/from this
    list re-enables or stops processing, respectively on those fields
    for all subsequent records.
    When a key value is in this list behavior can differ based on the
    [API[]{#LST7553ACFD_11}](0f330211-d3fb-3b01-532a-4edc4f684db6.htm)
    ProfileDirection:
    - [Export](0f330211-d3fb-3b01-532a-4edc4f684db6.htm): future result
      values for those fields will be [[]{#LST7553ACFD_12}]{.keyword}
    - [Import](0f330211-d3fb-3b01-532a-4edc4f684db6.htm): future
      [Element]{.nolink}s will skip this field when processing

  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------

[]{.introStyle}

::: summary
Extracts data from [document]{.parameter} via an
[Export](0f330211-d3fb-3b01-532a-4edc4f684db6.htm) profile.

Note that when [SelectionScope]{.nolink} of
[exportProfileName]{.parameter} is either
[View](68f48d72-e10d-ad1a-3de7-82b7b7d9d97a.htm) or
[Selection](68f48d72-e10d-ad1a-3de7-82b7b7d9d97a.htm), the current Revit
window context is used, so it is expected that the provided
[document]{.parameter} is the active [Document]{.nolink} within the
current Revit window.
:::

It contains a lookup with each matching item\'s [UniqueId]{.nolink} as
the outer key with the inner data being a lookup of each fully resolved
[DataProfileFieldDefinition]{.nolink}. The key for the inner lookup is
the [ColumnName]{.nolink} and the value is the fully resolved/expanded
[ParameterName]{.nolink} value.

When [SpecialParameterName]{.nolink} values are used, it is possible
that a single [Element]{.nolink} could produce multiple rows. When this
occurs the respective key of the return modifies the [UniqueId]{.nolink}
value of the \"extra\" rows to include a suffix. Use the
[GetUniqueId(String)](9303b41f-11e9-0689-b3f4-134757b71ee8.htm) method
to guarantee the appropriate [UniqueId]{.nolink} is pulled for each
respective entry.
